{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, ChatGPT showed promising results in a simulated Ophthalmic Knowledge Assessment Program (OKAP) exam [49].",
    "However, the average score of ChatGPT was 60.17% in the Membership of the Royal College of General Practitioners Applied Knowledge Test (AKT), which is below 70.4%, the mean passing threshold in the last 2 years [50].Furthermore, LLMs have been shown to be effective at making medical knowledge accessible to the public.In particular, a fine-tuned chatbot based on LLaMA demonstrated enhanced performance in identifying patients' needs and providing informed suggestions [51].",
    "In the realm of medical advice, ChatGPT generated educational documents, answered questions about allergy and immunology [52], and countered vaccine conspiracy theories [53].",
    "It can also answer the most frequently asked questions about the COVID-19 pandemic.",
    "Its overall responses to queries related to cognitive decline were equivalent to and, at times, more reliable than Google's [54]."
  ]
}